OpenWispr — vendored MLC-LLM / Apache TVM Android runtime (:mlc4j)
================================================================

This module ("mlc4j") is vendored from the MLC-LLM project and Apache TVM, both
licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (see the LICENSE file in this
directory). It is included here to run the on-device LLM cleanup model on the
Adreno GPU via OpenCL.

Upstream sources:
  - MLC-LLM     — https://github.com/mlc-ai/mlc-llm        (Apache-2.0)
  - Apache TVM  — https://github.com/apache/tvm            (Apache-2.0)

Files in this module derived from the above (unmodified or lightly adapted for
packaging — build.gradle, Kotlin/JVM target):
  - src/main/java/ai/mlc/mlcllm/MLCEngine.kt
  - src/main/java/ai/mlc/mlcllm/OpenAIProtocol.kt
  - src/main/java/ai/mlc/mlcllm/JSONFFIEngine.java
  - output/tvm4j_core.jar                       (Apache TVM Java runtime)
  - output/arm64-v8a/libtvm4j_runtime_packed.so (build artifact; gitignored)

The compiled model library statically linked into libtvm4j_runtime_packed.so is
generated by MLC-LLM's compiler; see ../REGENERATE.md for the build pinning.

Local modification: the prefill matmul dlight schedule in TVM was patched for
Adreno (M-tile + shared-memory staging); see openWispr research/adreno-prefill-mtile-fix.patch.

